      <td valign="top" width="519" height="703"><!--mstheme--><font face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica"><font size="+1" face="Comic Sans MS">Hello,</font>
        <p style="COLOR: rgb(255,0,0)" align="justify"><font color="#000000"><font size="+1" face="Comic Sans MS">I
        am Chirag Vaidya, a Computer Engineer working with <a href="http://www.marconi.com/html/products/broadbandroutingswitching.htm">Broadband
        Routing and Switching (BBRS)</a> division of <a href="http://www.marconi.com"> Marconi</a>.
        Presently I am working on <a href="http://www.marconi.com/html/products/integratedaccessdevicesiads.htm"> Integrated Access Devices
        (IAD)</a> and <a href="http://www.marconi.com/html/products/forerunnerheatmnics.htm">Solaris
        ATM Adapters</a> and am
        located in <a href="http://www.city.pittsburgh.pa.us">Pittsburgh</a>, <a href="http://www.state.pa.us/">Pennsylvania</a>, USA.</font><br>
        <font size="+1" face="Comic Sans MS">Before this I was working in Voice
        Over IP team at <a href="http://www.hssworld.com"> Hughes Software Systems
        (HSS)</a>
        at Gurgaon, India, a subsidiary of <a href="http://www.hns.com"> Hughes Network Systems
        (HNS)</a>, <a href="http://www.state.md.us">Maryland</a>, USA.</font></font></p>
        <p style="COLOR: rgb(255,0,0)" align="justify"><font color="#000000"><font size="+1" face="Comic Sans MS">Well
        to start with I belong to a small beautiful valley&nbsp; of <a href="http://www.himachalonline.com"> Himachal
        Pradesh</a> called <a href="http://www.himachalonline.com/mandi/index.htm"> Mandi</a> which is situated on the bank of river Beas. I was
        born in the &quot;Queen of Hills&quot; <a href="http://www.himachalonline.com/shimla/index.htm">Simla</a>. Whole of my schooling took
        place in Mandi and I completed my XIIth from Vallabh Govt. PG College
        Mandi.</font><br>
        <font size="+1" face="Comic Sans MS">I joined <a href="http://www.nsit.ac.in/"> Delhi Institute of
        Technology (now renamed to Netaji Subhas Institute of Technology)</a>, Delhi
        for a Degree in Computer Sciences in 1994. In College, I played active
        role in organizing all the cultural events, college festivals and
        technical Seminars. I was a members of college Volley ball team and
        represented college in various University and Delhi Colleges'
        tournaments. I even was the member of college Cultural Committee.
        Considering my efficiency in organizing things, I was voted for the
        Treasurer of IEEE DIT chapter and organized the DIT Technical fest known
        as DITECH, in which various colleges from all over India participated.
        For my contributions, I was adjudged as the best all-round student
        passed out of my Institute in the year 1998.</font></font></p>
        <p align="justify"><font size="+1" face="Comic Sans MS" color="#000000">After
        enjoying a good many four years in DIT, I came out in this harsh world
        to make a place for myself and Hughes &amp; then Marconi provided me
        this opportunity.</font><!--mstheme--></font></td>
    </tr>
